context: <b8_0>The Central African Republic<b8_0/> (CAR; Sango: Ködörösêse tî Bêafrîka; French: République centrafricaine  pronounced: [ʁepyblik sɑ̃tʁafʁikɛn], or Centrafrique [sɑ̃tʀafʁik]) is a landlocked country in <a0_0><b5_0>Central Africa<b5_0/><a0_0/>. It is bordered by <a1_0>Chad<a1_0/> to the north, Sudan to the northeast, South Sudan to the east, the Democratic Republic of the Congo and <a2_0>the Republic of the Congo<a2_0/> to the south and <a3_0>Cameroon<a3_0/> to the west. The CAR covers a land area of about <b6_0>620,000 square kilometres<b6_0/> (240,000 sq mi) and had an estimated population of around <a4_0><b7_0><b9_0>4.7 million<b9_0/><b7_0/><a4_0/> as of 2014[update].
